ZE=1>204</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>1/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>8:57:24 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.iland.net/~jewell/Ed_thumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Decision concerning LoM, 1/24 Fear raid</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">On Jan 24, LoM was the posting entity headed into Fear.  Being that there was a server reset, CT and draco were both up.  LoM felt confident that they would be able to handle this within the time allowed, but it ended up that this was not so.  <br>
<br>
Nanilya, with my endorsement as I had to camp, was in-zone to see how things were going.  Neither she nor I (no, I did not disturb the raiders overly much as the replies I received were very short and rather distracted...and I did not wish to cause unfounded interference) were getting much information from those within the zone, and it seemed to be a tad evasive...that being why Nanilya was in-zone.  This caused LoM to feel hovered over (they remember another instance in which it was intrusive, unlike this instance).<br>
<br>
But I digress.  Time pressed on, and before they are fully aware, it's 2am PST, CT yet lived, and Dues Factum was calling them on time...which they respected from most accounts.<br>
<br>
Solarees has come before this community and admits his error in judgement.  In speaking with many people, I've concluded that while quite against the rules of leaving the god up, that this was a mistake due to heavy CR, not lack of ability (I cannot address either the ability or lack thereof but have to have faith that they felt capable) to kill Cazic.<br>
<br>
The Calendar Admins were called upon to make a decision regarding the consequences of LoMs actions, and discussion amongst us began.  Tho we had not completely (didn't get input from all) discussed it, I felt comfortable enough from our prior discussions about various matters that what I put forth here is agreeable with my fellows.<br>
<br>
My original thought was to cancel all raids and ban LoM from posting until Feb 15.  I spoke at some length to Solarees in the attempt to come to some resolution of this matter.  He has admitted his error.  He has apologized to this community for not following the call-in rule.  During the course of our conversation, I found Solarees both honest and straight with me (tho perhaps a tad reserved, but that was a result of being called on the carpet), and I believe that he should have a touch of leniency.  He asked if there were some alternative, and I asked what he would suggest.  This is what was decided:<br>
<br>
LoM will keep their Hate raid on Feb 10.  They will not be able to post any Fear raids, nor any further Hate raids, until Feb 25.  Their Hate raid will be scrutinized, I am sure, due to this incident.  I warned Solarees that any infraction on that raid would result in more serious reprecussions.</font><P><center><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="5" color="#C0C0C0"><strong>Edwina Nytengayle<br> </strong></font></center>

